avgSpeed_corr = lambda x: x.corrwith(x['avgSpeed'])
by_hour =roadtraffic.groupby(lambda x: x.hour)
by_hour.apply(avgSpeed_corr)

grouped = roadtraffic.groupby('hour')
get_wavg = lambda g: np.average(g['avgSpeed'], weights=g['vehicleCount'])
grouped.apply(get_wavg)

%pyspark
import statsmodels.api as sm

def regression(data, yvar, xvars):
  Y = data[yvar]
  X = data[xvars]
  X['intercept'] = 1.
  result = sm.OLS(Y,X).fit()
  return result.params
by_hour.apply(regression,'avgSpeed',['vehicleCount'])
